KubeSwift Architecture
Purpose
This document explains the internal architecture of KubeSwift, a Kubernetes-native virtual machine runtime built on Cloud Hypervisor.
It is intended for:
contributors
operators
AI assistants helping develop the project
It describes:
system architecture
runtime lifecycle
controller behavior
networking model
image pipeline
debugging surfaces

System Overview
KubeSwift allows Kubernetes users to run virtual machines as native Kubernetes workloads.
Each VM is represented by a SwiftGuest custom resource and executed inside a launcher pod running Cloud Hypervisor.
The architecture separates:

Control Plane
Runtime Plane
Guest VM


High-Level Architecture

User
 │
 │ kubectl / helm / swiftctl
 │
 ▼
Kubernetes API Server
 │
 │ CRDs
 │
 ▼
KubeSwift Controllers
 │
 │ create launcher pod
 │
 ▼
SwiftGuest Pod
 │
 ├─ network-init (init container)
 │
 └─ launcher container (swiftletd)
        │
        ▼
     Cloud Hypervisor
        │
        ▼
